@startuml 10C-activity-candidate-scoring
' CVerify — Deterministic candidate scoring model.
' Verified against:
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/scoring_engine.py
'       score_candidate_deterministic:455-560 (inline policy defaults:462-471,
'           scoring_policy.json load attempt:472-478, proficiency fallback:482-512,
'           has_verified_repos:514, verified:515-521, self-declared:526-533,
'           aggregate:534-539, cohort normalise:541-542, uncertainty band:543)
'       calculate_verified_score:29-195  (log1p impact with company/role scalers:150-180)
'       calculate_self_declared_score:197-322 (leadership multiplier 1.15:~160)
'       aggregate_scores:323-385 (0.85/0.15 blend, 0.40 ceiling:336-349)
'       normalize_score_to_cohort:387-422 (11-point linear interpolation)
'       calculate_uncertainty_band:424-440 (margin 5% .. 20%)
'       classify_seniority:442-453
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/cohort_snapshot_v1.json (cohortVersion v1.0.0,
'       snapshotDate 2026-06-16, totalCandidates 1000, 11 percentile bins)
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/tasks/career_level.py
'       CareerLevelGate:390-505 (dependencies ["L2-005"]:400, hard floors:428-460,
'       Type-1 repo requirement:461-471, deterministic overwrite of the LLM output:485-492)
'   CVerify.AI/app/pipelines/candidate/tasks/composer.py:58, :113 (same JSON paths, different depth)
' Ground truth: GROUND-TRUTH.md §6.3.

title CVerify — Candidate Scoring (deterministic 5-dimension model)

start
:score_candidate_deterministic(cv, repository_assessments,
skill_proficiencies, historical scores);

partition "Policy resolution" {
  :start from the **inlined default policy**
  skillDepth   weight 0.35, scale_A 22.0, scale_B 0.05
  ownership    weight 0.25, scale_A 22.0, scale_B 0.20
  architecture weight 0.20, scale_A 22.0, scale_B 0.05
  problemSolving weight 0.12, scale_A 22.0, scale_B 0.10
  impact       weight 0.08, scale_A 20.0, scale_B 1.00;
  if (scoring_policy.json exists at the loaded path?) then (yes)
    :override the defaults;
  else (no)
    :keep the inlined defaults;
  endif
  note right #ffdddd
    GROUND-TRUTH §6.3: **`scoring_policy.json` does not exist at the path
    the code loads it from.** Three call sites each carry their own copy of
    these defaults, so the "configurable policy" is inert and any drift
    between the three copies is silent.
  end note
}

if (skill_proficiencies supplied by L2-002?) then (no)
  :derive them from repository skillAttributions —
  average contributionWeight banded as
  >= 0.8 Expert (4.0) · >= 0.5 Practitioner (3.0)
  · >= 0.2 Working (2.0) · else Awareness (1.0);
endif

fork
  partition "Verified track (repository evidence)" {
    :skillDepth, ownership, architecture, problemSolving from
    repository capabilities, skill attributions and ownership signals;
    :verified projects = those linked to an analyzed repo or with
    verificationLevel AiAnalyzed / RepositoryLinked;
    :impact = log1p(scale_B x verified_months)
    x company_scale x role_scale x scale_A;
    note right
      company_scale is 1.15 if the free-text description mentions one of
      seven hardcoded employers (google, apple, facebook, meta, netflix,
      amazon, microsoft); role_scale is 1.6 / 1.4 / 1.2 / 0.8 from
      substring matches on the role title. Both are unverified strings the
      candidate typed — they scale a "verified" dimension.
    end note
    :score_verified = sum(dimension x weight);
  }
fork again
  partition "Self-declared track (CV only)" {
    :same five dimensions computed from CV skills, projects and experiences;
    :total_months from experiences (fallback: recompute from dates);
    :leadership_mult = 1.15 if any experience isLeadership;
    :impact = log1p(scale_B x total_months)
    x company_scale x role_scale x leadership_mult x scale_A;
    :score_self_declared = sum(dimension x weight);
  }
end fork

partition "Blend" {
  if (has_verified_repos — len(repository_assessments) > 0?) then (yes)
    :verified_weight = 0.85
    self_declared_weight = 0.15
    scale_ceiling = 1.00;
  else (no)
    :verified_weight = 0.00
    self_declared_weight = 1.00
    **scale_ceiling = 0.40**;
    note right
      The 0.40 ceiling is applied per dimension
      (`combine_dim` multiplies the blend by the ceiling), so a
      candidate with no verified repository can never exceed 40% of
      the scale on **any** dimension — the cap is structural, not a
      post-hoc clamp on the overall score.
      Note the gate is `len(repository_assessments) > 0`, not "at
      least one that succeeded", so a repo whose assessment failed
      still lifts the ceiling to 1.00.
    end note
  endif
  :combined[dim] = (verified[dim] x verified_weight
  + self_declared[dim] x self_declared_weight) x scale_ceiling;
  :overall = sum(combined[dim] x weight[dim]);
}

partition "Cohort normalisation" {
  if (cohort_snapshot_v1.json readable at the loaded path?) then (yes)
    :sort the percentile bins by score;
    if (raw <= first bin?) then (yes)
      :percentile = first bin;
    elseif (raw >= last bin?) then (yes)
      :percentile = last bin;
    else (no)
      :linear interpolation between the two surrounding
      of the 11 bins;
    endif
  else (no)
    :fallback — percentile = clamp(raw, 0, 100),
    cohortVersion "v0.0.0-fallback";
  endif
  note right #ffdddd
    The snapshot is synthetic: cohortVersion v1.0.0,
    snapshotDate 2026-06-16, `totalCandidates: 1000`, 11 hand-written
    bins. Percentiles are therefore relative to a fabricated cohort,
    not to the live user base.

    **Additionally verified here (beyond GROUND-TRUTH §6.3):** the path
    `scoring_engine.py` builds is `dirname(dirname(__file__))` =
    `app/pipelines/`, but the file actually lives at
    `app/pipelines/candidate/cohort_snapshot_v1.json`. From
    `scoring_engine.py` **both** JSON files miss and the fallbacks fire.
    The same expression in `tasks/composer.py` and
    `tasks/improvement_engine.py` is one directory deeper and resolves
    correctly — so the cohort snapshot loads for those two callers and
    not for this one. Same constant, two different behaviours.
  end note
}

partition "Uncertainty band" {
  :ratio = clamp(self_declared_score / max(combined_score, 1.0), 0, 1);
  :margin = 5.0 + 15.0 x ratio
  (+/-5% fully verified, +/-20% fully self-declared);
  :cohortPercentileRange = { min: percentile - margin,
  max: percentile + margin, margin }
  clamped to [0, 100];
}

partition "Seniority classification (heuristic)" {
  :classify_seniority(complexity, leadership, maturity, ownership)
  L5 Principal >= 85 / 80 / 85 / 75
  L4 Staff     >= 75 / 65 / 75 / 60
  L3 Senior    >= 55 / 40 / 60 / 45
  L2 Middle    >= 30 / 15 / 35 / 30
  L1 Junior    >= 10 /  - / 15 / 15
  else Intern;
}

partition "L2-006 CareerLevelGate — hard floors that override the LLM" {
  :input = calibratedLevel from L2-005,
  plus architectureScore, problemSolvingScore, impactScore;
  if (calibratedLevel == L3?) then (yes)
    if (architecture < 100?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L2;
    endif
    if (problemSolving < 80?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L2;
    endif
  elseif (calibratedLevel == L4?) then (yes)
    if (architecture < 180?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L3;
    endif
    if (impact < 110?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L3;
    endif
  elseif (calibratedLevel == L5?) then (yes)
    if (architecture < 250?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L4;
    endif
    if (impact < 150?) then (yes)
      :violation; final_level = L4;
    endif
  endif
  if (final_level in {L3, L4, L5} and no repository with
      cvVerificationLevel "AiAnalyzed" or trustLevel 3?) then (yes)
    :violation "Seniority levels (L3+) require at least one
    verified Type 1 (AI Analyzed) repository";
    :final_level = L2;
  endif
  :gate_passed = (no violations);

  :call Claude with the gate prompt and the violation list;
  :**overwrite the model's answer** —
  ai_data["gatePassed"]      = gate_passed
  ai_data["finalLevel"]      = final_level
  ai_data["finalLevelLabel"] = level_map[final_level]
  ai_data["finalScore"]      = calibrated_score
  ai_data["gateViolations"]  = gate_violations
  (gateRationale replaced too when the gate failed);
  note right #ffdddd
    The Claude call happens **after** the decision is already made and
    its structured verdict is unconditionally discarded. Only the
    unlisted narrative fields of the model's JSON survive, so the LLM
    can never raise or lower the level — it can only describe it, and
    its prose can contradict the numbers if it disagrees.
    A malformed response still fails the whole task, because
    `_extract_json` raises after the json_repair fallback.
  end note
  :emit LEVEL_ESTIMATE_UPDATED pipeline event;
}

:return candidateScore, dimension breakdown, finalLevel /
finalLevelLabel, cohortPercentile, cohortVersion,
cohortPercentileRange, careerLevelConfidence (hardcoded 0.85);
stop

note bottom #ffdddd
  Two further inert artefacts on this path (GROUND-TRUTH §6.3, §6.6):
  * `risk_policy.json` declares `type_multipliers`, which is **never read**;
  * `weighted_scoring_engine.py` (repository line) has **zero importers**.
  And per §6.1, no SFIA level or O*NET code participates in any of the
  arithmetic above — `onetCode` is written to output and never read.
end note

@enduml
